[{"category":"section","location":"main-docs.html#Main-Documentation","page":"← Documentation","text":"<script>\nwindow.location.href = \"../index.html\";\n</script>\n<p>Click here if not redirected: <a href=\"../index.html\">Main Documentation</a></p>","title":"Main Documentation"},{"category":"section","location":"index.html#SciBmad.jl-API-Reference","page":"API Reference","text":"This documentation is a work in progress. Please see the examples and slides until this is complete.\n\n<p>For full documentation, see <a href=\"../index.html\">Documentation</a> or <a href=\"../user-guide/index.html\">User Guide</a>.</p>","title":"SciBmad.jl API Reference"},{"category":"section","location":"index.html#Index","page":"API Reference","text":"","title":"Index"},{"category":"section","location":"index.html#SciBmad.jl","page":"API Reference","text":"","title":"SciBmad.jl"},{"category":"section","location":"index.html#Beamlines.jl","page":"API Reference","text":"","title":"Beamlines.jl"},{"category":"method","location":"index.html#SciBmad.newton!-Union{Tuple{S}, Tuple{X}, Tuple{Y}, Tuple{Function, Y, X, Any}} where {Y, X, S}","page":"API Reference","text":"newton!(f!, y, x; reltol=1e-13, abstol=1e-13,  max_iter=100, backend=DI.AutoForwardDiff(), check_stable=Val{false}())\n\nFinds roots of f!(y, x) using Newton's method. y and x will be mutated during solution. x will contain the result.\n\nArguments\n\nf!: Function that mutates y in place with the residual vector\ny: Residual vector\nx: Initial guess\n\nKeyword arguments\n\nabstol: Convergence absolute tolerance (default: 1e-13)\nreltol: Convergence relative tolerance (default: 1e-13)\nmax_iter: Maximum number of iterations (default: 100)\n\nReturns NamedTuple containing newton search results.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SciBmad.newton!"},{"category":"method","location":"index.html#SciBmad.rotate-Tuple{Union{AbstractMatrix, AbstractVector}, Union{AbstractMatrix, AbstractVector}}","page":"API Reference","text":"Rotates vector v by quaternion q.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SciBmad.rotate"},{"category":"method","location":"index.html#SciBmad.rotate_spins!-Tuple{AbstractMatrix, AbstractMatrix, AbstractMatrix}","page":"API Reference","text":"Given an N x 4 matrix quaternions `q` (e.g., from the `Bunch` struct),\nand an N x 3 matrix of initial spin 3-vectors `si`, rotates the spin \n3-vectors by its corresponding row in the quaternion matrix and fills \nthe N x 3 matrix `sf` with the result.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SciBmad.rotate_spins!"},{"category":"method","location":"index.html#SciBmad.rotate_spins-Tuple{AbstractMatrix, AbstractMatrix}","page":"API Reference","text":"Given an N x 4 matrix quaternions `q` (e.g., from the `Bunch` struct),\nand an N x 3 matrix of initial spin 3-vectors `si`, rotates the spin \n3-vectors by its corresponding row in the quaternion matrix and returns \na new spin matrix containing the final spin 3-vectors.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SciBmad.rotate_spins"},{"category":"type","location":"index.html#Beamlines.BMultipoleParams","page":"API Reference","text":"struct BMultipoleParams{T,N} <: AbstractParams\n\nStructure holding the magnetic multipole components of a lattice element. \n\nFields\n\n• n::SizedVector{N,T,Vector{T}}     # Vector of normal multipole components. \n• s::SizedVector{N,T,Vector{T}}     # Vector of skew multipole components. \n• tilt::SizedVector{N,T,Vector{T}}  # Vector of tilt components. \n• order::SVector{N,Int}             # Vector of the order of the components. \n• normalized::SVector{N,Bool}       # Vector of whether a multipole is normalized or not. \n• integrated::SVector{N,Bool}       # Vector of whether a multipole is integrated or not. \n\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Beamlines.BMultipoleParams"},{"category":"method","location":"index.html#Base.empty!-Tuple{Beamline}","page":"API Reference","text":"empty!(::Beamline)\n\nRemoves BeamlineParams from all elements in the Beamline and empties  the array of LineElements.\n\nWARNING: this is irreversible.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Base.empty!"},{"category":"method","location":"index.html#Beamlines.scalarize!-Tuple{Beamline}","page":"API Reference","text":"scalarize!(bl::Beamline)\n\nModifies the Beamline so all LineElement parameters are scalars and all  Beamline-level parameters are scalars.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Beamlines.scalarize!"},{"category":"method","location":"index.html#Beamlines.scalarize!-Tuple{Lattice}","page":"API Reference","text":"scalarize!(lat::Lattice)\n\nModifies the Lattice so all LineElement and Beamline parameters are scalars.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Beamlines.scalarize!"},{"category":"method","location":"index.html#Beamlines.scalarize!-Tuple{LineElement}","page":"API Reference","text":"scalarize!(ele::LineElement)\n\nModifies the LineElement so all element-level parameters are scalars\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Beamlines.scalarize!"}]
